  "prompt": "How do I prepare myself for screening?",
  "response": "The specific preparation for a screening depends on the type of screening. Here are some general tips for common screenings:\n\n1. Medical screening:\n- Follow instructions from your healthcare provider\n- Bring medical history and insurance information\n- Wear comfortable clothing\n- Be honest about symptoms and medical history\n\n2. Job screening:\n- Review job requirements\n- Prepare relevant documents\n- Practice interview skills\n- Research the company\n- Dress professionally\n\n3. Background screening:\n- Gather necessary documents\n- Check for accuracy of personal information\n- Be prepared to provide references\n- Be honest about past employment and history\n\n4. Health screenings:\n- Fast if required\n- Avoid certain medications if instructed\n- Stay hydrated\n- Wear loose, comfortable clothing\n- Bring list of current medications\n\n5. Security screening:\n- Know prohibited items\n- Arrive early\n- Have identification ready\n- Follow instructions from personnel\n- Be patient and cooperative\n\nWithout knowing the specific type of screening you're preparing for, these are general guidelines. For precise instructions, always consult the specific screening guidelines or ask the organizing entity.",
